t","data":[{"title":"The 92mph England fast bowler ready to move on from difficult debut","href":"/sport/cricket/articles/c392llypge3o","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"sport","lastUpdated":1777544953073,"firstUpdated":1777544953073,"topics":["Cricket"]},"tags":[],"description":"A stronger and faster Sonny Baker is ready to put last summer's difficult white-ball debuts for England behind him.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/4994/live/c85f2880-43e4-11f1-ac78-2112837ce2aa.jpg","altText":"Sonny Baker, wearing a cap, smiles during England training","width":4011,"height":2256}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:bbc:optimo:asset:c392llypge3o","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"Late kicks and sad farewells - Ulster and semi-final drama","href":"/sport/rugby-union/articles/cp3l3nr325eo","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"sport","lastUpdated":1777544489875,"firstUpdated":1777544489875,"topics":["Ulster"]},"tags":[],"description":"Ahead of Saturday's Challenge Cup semi-final against Exeter Chiefs, BBC Sport looks at how Ulster have fared in their last five attempts to reach a major final.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/6496/live/7c9451f0-447a-11f1-ac78-2112837ce2aa.png","altText":"James Hume dejected, Ian Madigan celebrates and Ruan Pienaar dejected","width":1600,"height":900}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:bbc:optimo:asset:cp3l3nr325eo","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"Former England defender Young to retire aged 40","href":"/sport/football/articles/c332vp461m0o","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"sport","lastUpdated":1777541650495,"firstUpdated":1777541650495,"topics":["Football"]},"tags":[],"description":"Ashley Young will end his playing career at Ipswich after saying it will be \"23 years and out\" at the end of this season.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/4ac3/live/422242c0-4475-11f1-b545-b533bcf4cad2.jpg","altText":"Former England defender Ashley Young in a blue Ipswich Town shirt, clapping his hands","width":1729,"height":973}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:bbc:optimo:asset:c332vp461m0o","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"Parker leaves Burnley after relegation","href":"/sport/football/articles/c332vpz2kgmo","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"sport","lastUpdated":1777541331241,"firstUpdated":1777539854155,"topics":["Burnley"]},"tags":[],"description":"Burnley head coach Scott Parker leaves the club following talks with the club's hierarchy.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/fcb6/live/2161ae10-4478-11f1-b545-b533bcf4cad2.jpg","altText":"Scott Parker holds his face","width":768,"height":432}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:bbc:optimo:asset:c332vpz2kgmo","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""}],"sectionTitleProps":{"link":"https://www.bbc.com/sport","linkType":"external"}},{"title":"Health","data":[{"title":"Nine ways to cope with your seasonal allergies","href":"/future/article/20260423-hay-fever-nine-tips-for-coping-better-with-pollen","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"features","lastUpdated":1777370400000,"firstUpdated":1777370400000,"topics":["Future"]},"tags":[],"description":"From the most effective medications to the most common triggers to avoid, we examine science-backed advice that should reduce your seasonal suffering.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/1920xn/p0nh0l0r.jpg","altText":"A boy and a girl run joyously through a field (Credit: Getty Images)","width":1920,"height":1080}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:wwverticals:article:future/article/20260423-hay-fever-nine-tips-for-coping-better-with-pollen","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"How enjoying your food could help you lose weight","href":"/future/article/20260424-diet-why-enjoying-your-food-is-key-to-weight-loss","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"features","lastUpdated":1777284000000,"firstUpdated":1777284000000,"topics":["Future"]},"tags":[],"description":"The mind-body connection can shape our appetite because our expectation of what we've eaten influences the brain's perceptions of hunger and satiation.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/1920xn/p0ngv4hc.jpg","altText":"A woman with dark curly hair biting down with enjoyment on an tangerine segment (Credit: Getty Images)","width":1920,"height":1080}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:wwverticals:article:future/article/20260424-diet-why-enjoying-your-food-is-key-to-weight-loss","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"Aspirin can reduce the risk of cancer - and we're starting to understand why","href":"/future/article/20260420-cancer-how-aspirin-may-be-a-powerful-new-weapon-against-tumours","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"features","lastUpdated":1776765600000,"firstUpdated":1776765600000,"topics":["Future"]},"tags":[],"description":"The 4,000-year-old drug, most commonly used to treat pain, prevents certain tumours from forming and spreading across the body – findings that are already changing health policies.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/1920xn/p0nfjf6b.jpg","altText":"A close up of someone pouring two tablets from a bottle of aspirin (Credit: Getty Images)","width":2222,"height":1250}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:wwverticals:article:future/article/20260420-cancer-how-aspirin-may-be-a-powerful-new-weapon-against-tumours","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"Is AI making us forget how to think?","href":"/future/article/20260417-ai-chatbots-could-be-making-you-stupider","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"features","lastUpdated":1776679200000,"firstUpdated":1776679200000,"topics":["Future"]},"tags":[],"description":"As large language models take over more and more cognitive tasks, researchers are warning this mental outsourcing comes with a cost.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/raw/p0nfsyr1.jpg","altText":"A phone with ChatGPT on the screen with the words \"Hey there, what are we digging into?\" displayed (Credit: Getty Images)","width":1920,"height":1080}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:wwverticals:article:future/article/20260417-ai-chatbots-could-be-making-you-stupider","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""}],"sectionTitleProps":{"link":"https://www.bbc.com/health","linkType":"internal"}},{"title":"Culture","data":[{"title":"Stephen Fry sues tech conference for up to £100,000 after falling off stage","href":"/news/articles/cvgzr2yy6vro","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"news","lastUpdated":1777481124887,"firstUpdated":1777481124887,"topics":["Culture"]},"tags":[],"description":"The star said he broke his leg, hip, pelvis and a \"bunch of ribs\" at the CogX convention in 2023.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/f222/live/6b392040-43ba-11f1-a5aa-c74cdbf526ae.jpg","altText":"Sir Stephen Fry in a pink shirt, gold tie and maroon jacket, at the premiere of Treasure during the 2024 Tribeca Festival","width":4165,"height":2343}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:bbc:optimo:asset:cvgzr2yy6vro","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"Tupac's family files wrongful death lawsuit in LA","href":"/news/articles/c0l28d517gjo","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"news","lastUpdated":1777464298074,"firstUpdated":1777464298074,"topics":["Culture"]},"tags":[],"description":"The suit seeks to uncover several \"co-conspirators\" who may have been involved in the star's death.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/41a5/live/302db840-43aa-11f1-9d89-8526d1435c1c.jpg","altText":"Tupac Shakur poses for photos backstage after his performance at the Regal Theater in Chicago, Illinois in March 1994. ","width":2312,"height":1301}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:bbc:optimo:asset:c0l28d517gjo","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"Laura Dern replaces Helena Bonham Carter in The White Lotus","href":"/news/articles/cx218w742jzo","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"news","lastUpdated":1777455550020,"firstUpdated":1777455550020,"topics":["Culture"]},"tags":[],"description":"The British actress left the hit show due to creative differences shortly after filming began.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/3296/live/5012d8b0-43b5-11f1-bd52-e755d604ece4.jpg","altText":"Laura dern headshot on the left and Helena Bonham Carter headshot on the right both at red carpet events looking  glamorous","width":976,"height":549}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:bbc:optimo:asset:cx218w742jzo","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"Billie Eilish puts Manchester at centre of new 3D concert film","href":"/news/articles/c794wv4rd50o","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"news","lastUpdated":1777421339716,"firstUpdated":1777421339716,"topics":["Culture"]},"tags":[],"description":"Teaming up with filmmaking giant James Cameron, the superstar creates a unique love letter to her fans.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/6754/live/6c1b1c40-4340-11f1-ac31-67f7e9c4da73.jpg","altText":"Billie Eilish, wearing a black blazer and blue shirt, at the premier with a blue screen behind her.","width":1000,"height":562}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:bbc:optimo:asset:c794wv4rd50o","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""}],"sectionTitleProps":{"link":"https://www.bbc.com/culture","linkType":"internal"}},{"title":"Travel","data":[{"title":"Petition seeks rules change for pets on planes","href":"/news/articles/clyxlj9277eo","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"news","lastUpdated":1777439543114,"firstUpdated":1777439543114,"topics":["Hull \u0026 East Yorkshire"]},"tags":[],"description":"A petition to change the rules is being back by the owners of one of Britain’s most famous dogs.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/7d5b/live/c8bd7d80-3ef4-11f1-95e9-c9f2031e3375.jpg","altText":"A striking-looking dog, which is a pug and Chinese crested cross, sits on a white pillow on an aeroplane seat in front of a oval window through which the blue sky can be seen. The dog has wild, white fur, a long red tongue and big brown eyes. It is wearing a red hooded jumper.","width":1536,"height":864}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:bbc:optimo:asset:clyxlj9277eo","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"Scots backpacker stuck 'in limbo' in Thailand over mobile phone 'mistake'","href":"/news/articles/c1e2pvygv20o","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"news","lastUpdated":1777412760048,"firstUpdated":1777412760048,"topics":["Edinburgh, Fife \u0026 East"]},"tags":[],"description":"Rory McColl had his passport confiscated after what he claims was a mix-up and faces a three month wait for a court hearing.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/1b10/live/07356800-3fbf-11f1-b61b-1d0ccf7b6022.png","altText":"Rory McColl , who is wearing a black baseball cap, takes a selfie in front of a stone elephant and a historic building","width":480,"height":270}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:bbc:optimo:asset:c1e2pvygv20o","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"Where to travel in Europe without high costs and massive crowds","href":"/travel/article/20260427-where-europe-still-feels-worth-it-this-summer","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"features","lastUpdated":1777381200000,"firstUpdated":1777381200000,"topics":["Travel"]},"tags":[],"description":"From Latvia to the Balkan coast, these destinations offer the beauty, culture and atmosphere travellers want – without the price or crowds.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/1024xn/p0ngtqjf.jpg","altText":"Whitewashed buildings with terracotta roofs and a church bell tower on a mountainside on Albania's Adriatic Coast (Credit: Getty Images)","width":1920,"height":1080}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:wwverticals:article:travel/article/20260427-where-europe-still-feels-worth-it-this-summer","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"What it's like to drive Route 66 in an EV","href":"/travel/article/20260424-what-its-like-to-drive-route-66-in-an-ev","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"features","lastUpdated":1777208400000,"firstUpdated":1777208400000,"topics":["Travel"]},"tags":[],"description":"As Route 66 turns 100, a growing charger network is making the Mother Road drivable by EV. But does the classic American road trip still feel the same without petrol?","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/1920xn/p0ngf2bt.jpg","altText":"A male action figure in a green filling station uniform raises his hand in greeting in front of Route 66 signs (Credit: Serenity Strull/ BBC/ Getty Images)","width":3745,"height":2107}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:wwverticals:article:travel/article/20260424-what-its-like-to-drive-route-66-in-an-ev","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""}],"sectionTitleProps":{"link":"https://www.bbc.com/travel","linkType":"internal"}}],"playlistMode":false},{"type":"advertisement","model":{"adType":"horizontal"},"incrementedType":"mid_6"},{"type":"montana","content":[{"title":"Chris Hemsworth's deeply emotional journey with his father","href":"/reel/video/p0myl6m3/watch","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"video","subtype":"reels","lastUpdated":1777525200000,"firstUpdated":1777525200000,"topics":["Film \u0026 TV"]},"tags":[],"description":"Chris Hemsworth tells Graham Norton how he made a documentary about his dad's Alzheimer's treatment.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/1920xn/p0mylgmh.jpg","altText":"Chris Hemsworth's deeply emotional journey across Australia with his father","width":1920,"height":1080,"duration":256}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:gnlvideoproject:video:p0myl6m3","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""}],"collectionId":"895d3e77-e6a3-41b3-bf71-6b9bd00f94ef","sectionTitleProps":{"link":"https://www.bbc.com/video","linkType":"internal"},"paginationData":{"page":0,"pageSize":1,"total":50},"title":"Watch","summary":"","disableAutoPlay":false,"style":"dark","innerCollections":[],"playlistMode":false},{"type":"custom-component","model":{"customComponentName":"regional-news-selection-component"}},{"type":"wyoming","content":[],"collectionId":"","sectionTitleProps":{},"paginationData":{"page":0,"pageSize":0,"total":0},"title":"","summary":"","disableAutoPlay":false,"innerCollections":[{"title":"Arts","data":[{"title":"The English heiress who masterminded 'one of the largest art heists in history'","href":"/culture/article/20260423-the-wealthy-english-heiress-who-stole-art-for-the-ira","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"features","lastUpdated":1777285858175,"firstUpdated":1777285858175,"topics":["Culture"]},"tags":[],"description":"Rose Dugdale rejected her privileged background and joined the IRA. In April 1974, reported the BBC, she took part in \"one of the largest art heists in history\".","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/1920xn/p0ng33c9.jpg","altText":"A black-and-white image of Rose Dugdale with her fist raised (Credit: Alamy)","width":2000,"height":1125}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:wwverticals:article:culture/article/20260423-the-wealthy-english-heiress-who-stole-art-for-the-ira","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"The enchanting history of Oxford University's 750-year-old library ","href":"/culture/article/20260423-the-enchanting-story-of-oxfords-medieval-library","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"features","lastUpdated":1777023589586,"firstUpdated":1777023589586,"topics":["Culture"]},"tags":[],"description":"Predating the Aztec Empire, Merton College Library in Oxford has been used by everyone from celebrated 14th-Century mathematicians to JRR Tolkien.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/1920xn/p0ng67l5.jpg","altText":"A walkway in the library of Merton College Oxford, lined with rows of bookcases and a globe at the end (Credit: Courtesy of the Warden and Fellows of Merton College Oxford)","width":2032,"height":1143}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:wwverticals:article:culture/article/20260423-the-enchanting-story-of-oxfords-medieval-library","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"10 intimate images of a lost, decadent 1930s Paris","href":"/culture/article/20260414-10-of-the-most-iconic-images-of-pariss-secret-night-time-world","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"features","lastUpdated":1776337200000,"firstUpdated":1776337200000,"topics":["Culture"]},"tags":[],"description":"Moving \"from the slums to the exclusive salons\", Brassaï captured the brothels, gay bars and backstreets of Paris's hazy night-time in its radical inter-war years.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/1920xn/p0nd9nkj.jpg","altText":"A black and white image shows a couple in the corner of a booth in a small Paris cafe with their faces close together as if they are about to kiss(Credit: Estate Brassai/ Succession Philippe Ribeyrolles)","width":2200,"height":1238}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:wwverticals:article:culture/article/20260414-10-of-the-most-iconic-images-of-pariss-secret-night-time-world","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"Why this 16th-Century painting isn't what it seems","href":"/culture/article/20260408-why-this-16th-century-painting-isnt-what-it-seems","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"features","lastUpdated":1775728853663,"firstUpdated":1775728853663,"topics":["Culture"]},"tags":[],"description":"Overpainted images hidden inside Raphael's 16th-Century Portrait of a Young Woman with a Unicorn show how the image of the ideal woman has been carefully controlled by men.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/1920xn/p0nc9mwv.jpg","altText":"Side-by-side image of monotoned and coloured versions of Raphael's Portrait of a Young Woman with a Unicorn (Credit: Alamy/ Galleria Borghese)","width":1920,"height":1080}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:wwverticals:article:culture/article/20260408-why-this-16th-century-painting-isnt-what-it-seems","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""}],"sectionTitleProps":{"link":"https://www.bbc.com/arts","linkType":"internal"}},{"title":"Earth","data":[{"title":"Chernobyl’s wildlife: Surviving in a poisoned land","href":"/future/article/20260424-chernobyl-wildlife-forty-years-on","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"features","lastUpdated":1777197600000,"firstUpdated":1777197600000,"topics":["Future"]},"tags":[],"description":"It's 40 years since the Chernobyl disaster. This is what it has meant for wildlife living around the devastated nuclear power plant.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/1920xn/p0ngd8ng.jpg","altText":"A fox looking to its right while standing in front of a Soviet era sign reading Pripyat 1970 (Credit: Getty Images)","width":1920,"height":1080}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:wwverticals:article:future/article/20260424-chernobyl-wildlife-forty-years-on","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"The abandoned vehicles in Chernobyl's 'dead zone'","href":"/future/article/20260424-the-eerie-abandoned-vehicles-in-chernobyls-dead-zone","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"features","lastUpdated":1777111200000,"firstUpdated":1777111200000,"topics":["Future"]},"tags":[],"description":"A huge armada of vehicles were used to clean up the radioactive aftermath of the Chernobyl disaster 40 years ago. Many of them still lie rusting inside the exclusion zone.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/1024xn/p0ngf75f.jpg","altText":"Derelict Mil Mi-6 helicopter at Rassokha in 2006 (Credit: Phil Coomes/ BBC)","width":1920,"height":1080}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:wwverticals:article:future/article/20260424-the-eerie-abandoned-vehicles-in-chernobyls-dead-zone","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"Bees behaving strangely? It must be hurricane season","href":"/future/article/20260422-bees-and-breadfruit-how-fijians-predict-cyclones","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"features","lastUpdated":1777021300190,"firstUpdated":1777021300190,"topics":["Future"]},"tags":[],"description":"In Fiji in the South Pacific, farmers are reading nature's warning signs to predict hurricanes – from creeping Yam vines to hornets nesting.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/raw/p0ngcdw8.jpg","altText":"A man walks along a row of bright green crops, towards tree covered hilltops (Credit: Frankie Adkins)","width":1920,"height":1080}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:wwverticals:article:future/article/20260422-bees-and-breadfruit-how-fijians-predict-cyclones","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"Humpback whales were nearly wiped out. Now their numbers are skyrocketing","href":"/future/article/20260416-the-humpback-super-groups-swarming-the-seas","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"features","lastUpdated":1776733254788,"firstUpdated":1776733254788,"topics":["Future"]},"tags":[],"description":"On a misty morning in December, two photographers captured the images of 304 individual humpbacks – the highest number of large whales ever identified in a single day.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/raw/p0ngj34p.jpg","altText":"A super-group of humpback whales at the surface (Credit: ChrisFallows.com)","width":1920,"height":1080}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:wwverticals:article:future/article/20260416-the-humpback-super-groups-swarming-the-seas","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""}],"sectionTitleProps":{"link":"https://www.bbc.com/future-planet","linkType":"internal"}},{"title":"Video","data":[{"title":"Oil price creeps up further","href":"/reel/video/p0nh8p0v/watch","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"video","subtype":"reels","lastUpdated":1777472905731,"firstUpdated":1777472905731,"topics":["Opening Bell"]},"tags":[],"description":"A muted opening on Wall Street as the oil price creeps up further.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/1920xn/p0nh8xnf.jpg","altText":"Oil price creeps up further","width":1428,"height":803,"duration":132}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:gnlvideoproject:video:p0nh8p0v","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"What it takes to become one of the world's top-paid nannies","href":"/reel/video/p0chln6s/watch","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"video","subtype":"reels","lastUpdated":1777352400000,"firstUpdated":1777352400000,"topics":["Work"]},"tags":[],"description":"Norland College produces elite child carers who work for royal families and can earn more than doctors.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/1920xn/p0cjr862.jpg","altText":"Norland1","width":1579,"height":888,"duration":371}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:gnlvideoproject:video:p0chln6s","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"Five of the 'Magnificent Seven' tech firms to report soon","href":"/reel/video/p0ngwbwj/watch","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"video","subtype":"reels","lastUpdated":1777304200379,"firstUpdated":1777304200379,"topics":["Opening Bell"]},"tags":[],"description":"Brian Vendig at MJP Wealth Advisors says he would not get 'overly' excited about the AI‑led market rebound.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/1920xn/p0ngwv67.jpg","altText":"Tech reports expected this week","width":1412,"height":794,"duration":134}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:gnlvideoproject:video:p0ngwbwj","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"A sleeper train adventure through Europe","href":"/reel/video/p0n49kwy/watch","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"video","subtype":"reels","lastUpdated":1777266000000,"firstUpdated":1777266000000,"topics":["The Travel Show"]},"tags":[],"description":"The Travel Show finds out if it's still possible to get from Istanbul to Paris by sleeper train.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/1920xn/p0n49l74.jpg","altText":"A sleeper train adventure through Europe","width":1920,"height":1080,"duration":236}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:gnlvideoproject:video:p0n49kwy","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""}],"sectionTitleProps":{"link":"https://www.bbc.com/video","linkType":"internal"}},{"title":"World's Table","data":[{"title":"Which country can claim steak?","href":"/travel/article/20260402-which-country-can-claim-steak","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"features","lastUpdated":1775480400000,"firstUpdated":1775480400000,"topics":["Travel"]},"tags":[],"description":"From Japan to Argentina to the US, nations around the world have put their own stamp on the mouthwatering meat – making beef a destination in itself.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/1920xn/p0nbcrxn.jpg","altText":"A thick T-bone steak sits against a black background, scattered with red peppercorns, rock salt and herb (Credit: Alamy)s","width":1920,"height":1080}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:wwverticals:article:travel/article/20260402-which-country-can-claim-steak","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"Inside the Turkish city built on 'green gold'","href":"/travel/article/20260316-the-turkish-city-built-on-green-gold","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"features","lastUpdated":1773748800000,"firstUpdated":1773748800000,"topics":["Travel"]},"tags":[],"description":"For centuries, pistachios have defined Gaziantep. Today, they remain the most prized ingredient in Turkey's culinary capital – and the secret behind its legendary baklava.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/1920xn/p0n6zpt4.jpg","altText":"A tray of pistachio baklava over a bed of pistachios (Credit: Getty Images)","width":1920,"height":1080}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:wwverticals:article:travel/article/20260316-the-turkish-city-built-on-green-gold","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"The rare 'dinosaur egg' returning from extinction","href":"/travel/article/20260312-the-tasty-dinosaur-egg-returning-from-extinction","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"features","lastUpdated":1773403200000,"firstUpdated":1773403200000,"topics":["Travel"]},"tags":[],"description":"Asin tibuok is one of the world's rarest salts and it's only produced on one small island. But thanks to chefs and TikTokers, this prehistoric-looking orb is now being revived.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/1920xn/p0n6bsnl.jpg","altText":"An asin tibuok – egg-shaped salt packed into a ceramic case (Credit: National Commission for Culture and the Arts)","width":1920,"height":1080}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:wwverticals:article:travel/article/20260312-the-tasty-dinosaur-egg-returning-from-extinction","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"Congee to consommé: Why every culture has a healing broth","href":"/travel/article/20260304-why-every-culture-has-a-healing-broth","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"article","subtype":"features","lastUpdated":1772715600000,"firstUpdated":1772715600000,"topics":["Travel"]},"tags":[],"description":"Across cultures, broths have soothed illness, marked celebration and stretched scarce ingredients, long before they became a wellness trend.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/1024xn/p0n4jfcg.jpg","altText":"Bowl of tortellini soup in a light broth with a cutlery and a folded napkin beside it (Credit: Alamy)","width":1920,"height":1080}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"urn:pubpipe:wwverticals:article:travel/article/20260304-why-every-culture-has-a-healing-broth","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""}],"sectionTitleProps":{"link":"https://www.bbc.com/travel/worlds-table","linkType":"internal"}}],"playlistMode":false},{"type":"texas","content":[{"title":"Sign up to Tech Decoded","href":"https://www.bbc.com/newsletters?techdecoded\u0026at_bbc_team=studios\u0026at_medium=display\u0026at_objective=acquisition\u0026at_ptr_type=\u0026at_ptr_name=bbc.comhp\u0026at_format=Module\u0026at_link_origin=homepage\u0026at_campaign=techdecoded\u0026at_campaign_type=owned","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"customCard","topics":[]},"tags":[],"description":"Decode the biggest developments in global technology, in your inbox every Monday and Friday.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/raw/p0lr3sb2.jpg","altText":"Sign up to Tech Decoded","width":1920,"height":1080}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"custom-card:da3c57a3-c225-4720-b334-c179955d98a0:0","brandName":"","seriesName":"","seriesId":"","brandId":"","versionId":""},{"title":"Download the BBC app","href":"https://www.bbc.com/pages/download-the-bbc-app","isLiveNow":false,"metadata":{"contentType":"customCard","topics":[]},"tags":[],"description":"Click here to download the BBC app for Apple and Android devices.","image":{"type":"indexImage","model":{"blocks":{"src":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/raw/p0lr3t4c.png","altText":"Download the BBC app","width":1920,"height":1080}}},"relatedUrls":[],"id":"custom-card:da3c57a